The paper deals with deep learning and kernel methods, which are commonly studied in the machine learning subfield of computer science. Specifically, the paper proposes a method for efficient computation in Deep Kernel Networks (DKNs), which are a combination of deep neural networks and kernel methods. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the experiments are conducted on image datasets. The paper also involves unsupervised learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of deep neural networks suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new method for designing maps in Reproducing Kernel Hilbert Spaces, which could be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
